WEBVTT

00:07.087 --> 00:09.255
How great that we both
exercise in the mornings.

00:09.257 --> 00:10.890
I mean, we can spend time together

00:10.892 --> 00:12.509
and get our workouts in.

00:12.511 --> 00:15.395
I know. Today my boot camp,
tomorrow your beach run...

00:15.397 --> 00:17.263
or is it more like a leisurely stroll?

00:17.265 --> 00:19.766
Hey, there's nothing leisurely
about the way I stroll.

00:19.768 --> 00:21.317
I mean, that's...

00:21.319 --> 00:23.236
If you say "that's just the
way I stroll" I will hit you.

00:23.238 --> 00:24.737
- I wasn't going to.
- Yeah, you were.

00:24.739 --> 00:26.573
I just hope you can keep up with me.

00:26.575 --> 00:28.992
Oh, did I forget to mention
I hold the record

00:28.994 --> 00:31.578
for the 100-yard dash
at my high school in Providence?

00:31.580 --> 00:33.162
Oh, so you're already a pro?

00:33.164 --> 00:34.948
Then you won't need the gift I got you.

00:34.950 --> 00:36.566
You got me a gift?

00:36.568 --> 00:37.784
I always run...

00:37.786 --> 00:40.286
with a pedometer.

00:40.288 --> 00:41.621
You're gonna spoil me.

00:41.623 --> 00:43.706
Wait and see where I'm taking
you for dinner tonight.

00:43.708 --> 00:46.926
Oh, I have a meeting
with a referring doctor tonight.

00:46.928 --> 00:48.928
- Tomorrow?
- I'm on call.

00:48.930 --> 00:50.413
Oh, wait. So am I.

00:50.415 --> 00:53.933
Typical workaholic doctor.

00:53.935 --> 00:55.585
We can figure this out.

00:55.587 --> 00:57.804
What's the rest of the week like?

00:57.806 --> 00:59.255
Uh, the night after tomorrow,

00:59.257 --> 01:01.307
I'm supposed to see my dad
for dinner, but I could cancel.

01:01.309 --> 01:03.393
No. Family dinners are sacrosanct.

01:03.395 --> 01:05.111
And then the night after that,
I'm on call again.

01:05.113 --> 01:06.980
- Can I have my pedometer back?
- No.

01:06.982 --> 01:09.098
Look, either we have a relationship

01:09.100 --> 01:10.783
based solely on workout routines,

01:10.785 --> 01:12.986
or we make on-call nights work.

01:12.988 --> 01:14.120
Yeah.

01:14.122 --> 01:16.072
You know that diner on Clearview?

01:16.074 --> 01:17.490
Isn't the food supposed to be terrible?

01:17.492 --> 01:19.442
Oh, so much worse than terrible.

01:19.444 --> 01:21.777
But next door is my favorite bookstore.

01:21.779 --> 01:22.945
So, if one of us gets called away,

01:22.947 --> 01:24.414
the other can find something good to read.

01:24.416 --> 01:25.748
Oh.

01:25.750 --> 01:27.333
They have an amazing poetry section.

01:27.335 --> 01:29.218
Finally something we don't have in common.

01:29.220 --> 01:30.670
I'm a mystery-novel guy.

01:30.672 --> 01:32.589
Oh, I bet they have those there too.

01:32.591 --> 01:35.291
Then the terrible diner it is.

01:35.293 --> 01:37.760
You guys look tired, huh?
Didn't have your breakfast?

01:41.132 --> 01:43.799
Oh...

01:43.801 --> 01:45.985
How sweet.

01:45.987 --> 01:47.937
Do it on your own time!

01:47.939 --> 01:49.822
This is my time!

01:49.824 --> 01:51.524
- Okay.
- Get on line!

01:51.526 --> 01:53.326
You're loud.

01:53.328 --> 01:55.495
Synchronize! Come on!

01:55.497 --> 01:58.648
- Come on, guys.
- Got it.

